name: The Sneezing Burro of Mystery Mesa
Mickey and Donald and the Beanstalk

description: Albert Polansky has undertaken a crusade against magicians, mediums, astrologers and healers. For him they’re all charlatans exploiting naive people. Mister No takes him to witness the magic rites of Bahia: Macumba, Candomblé, Umbanda. But it’s the meeting with fiery Congo Vevé that will show Polansky that not all magicians are fakes. And some are really able to evoke demons and revive the dead…
name: Magia Nera

description: James Stanley is the great grandson of Sir Henry Morton Stanley, the man who saved the explorer Livingston. He wants to imitate his ancestor’s enterprise, but it’s all going to be fake, as a scam to worm money out of the papers and television. Mister No, who was guiding Stanley, discovers the trick and takes his revenge in his own way…
name: Uomini nella Giungla

description: Mister No returns to Bahia and sees the beautiful Miranda again, who hasn’t lost her habit of getting Mister No into trouble. Miranda’s man, Helio, is in contact with a secessionist organisation, led by Colonel Guimaraes, who wants to found the state of Novo Sertão. They are keeping alive the memory of the mythical Cangaceiros, and have taken possession of the head of Lampião, the legendary “King of Sertão”!
name: Il Re del Sertão

description: Patricia, Mister No’s archaeologist friend, together with other colleagues, is looking for the mysterious city Zeta, an outpost of the legendary Atlantis in Amazonia. The Englishman Percy Fawcett has already tried in vain to find the city. But a bitter surprise awaits the scholars: a destiny of death looms over the expedition. Maybe not even Mister No will be able to avoid it...
name: Un Mondo Perduto

description: Is it a dream or reality? On a journey in South-Africa Mister No finds himself projected into the past to the age of the legendary battle of Isandhlwana, fought between English soldiers and Zulu warriors. Only this time the English are led by General Custer (did he survive the massacre at Little Big Horn?) and among the Zulus there is Mister No’s old acquaintance: Dana Winter!
name: Zulu!

description: São Luis do Maranhão, 1950. Mister No has just arrived in Brazil and is strongly attracted by the alluring local beauties. But the most attractive woman is the blonde and enigmatic foreigner, Wendy Robertson: Her driver is Esse-Esse: it is their first meeting and the beautiful Wendy involves him in a passionate affair, friendship and death…
name: Dark Lady

description: There are still strange people in Manaus. One in particular is James Newman, a comic strip author, in love with the strip “Terry and the pirates” by Milton Caniff. Newman wants Mister No to be his guide in the Amazon jungle , in order to find ideas for his new stories. He is in search of adventure but reality is always different from fiction….
name: Avventura a Manaus

description: 1952. Mister No witnesses an unusual event, a violent explosion of brilliant light that nearly causes him to crash his plane. The news is read by the then child, Martin Mystère. 1993. The detective of the impossible and a seventy-year-old (but still on his toes) Mister No unite forces to resolve the mystery from years before. Two great and unusual heroes experience an adventure together!
name: Mister No & Martin Mystère - Fuga da Skynet

description: 1945 No sooner out of the military hospital in Atlantic City than Mister No has to go Albuquerque, in New Mexico, to deliver an affidavit in which a man officially admits to being the father of the individual named in the document. This enables the son of his deceased hospital ward companion, Mark Hollister, and of the Indio, Lathia, to inherit his father’s vast fortune. But the inheritance attracts others…
name: Le Iene

description: There is a wild beast in the heart of Amazonia and it is not the jaguar, it is a human being. It is the surgeon De Rovey who tears out the hearts of the Indios in the (always unsuccessful) attempt to transplant the hearts into the dying mobster Monteleone. Mister No wants to stop him, with the help of Dermott (Monteleone’s honest grandson) and the young surgeon Raver. However, remember the saying: you can’t go against one of your own…
name: I Diavoli Bianchi

description: Nevada desert, 1950. A still disappointed Mister No meets the characters that will change his life: Jonathan Eden and the young Oliver. From the former he will copy his look, (the famous sweater with a four-leafed clover), while thanks to the second, Mister No (in a certain sense) will fight in Korea!
name: Il Soldato Senza Nome

description: The grandfather is an old Indio, who tells his grandson a story set in the “great stone forest” (New York), in which two just men (Mister No and Esse-Esse) find themselves fighting on opposite sides. A story in which mystery and the unexplainable invade the Big Apple.
name: Giungla d'Asfalto

description: United States, late nineteen-thirties. Mister No is a young sixteen year old. His father is sentenced to prison for murder, and so Jerry decides to leave New York and catches a train to adventure. He finds it in Des Moines and he also finds new friends, a new love, and another bitter disappointment…
name: Un Giovane Americano

description: 1947. In Southern California, Mister No meets the Hell’s Angels (a motorcycle gang) headed by John Turner, the so called Sonny, and allows himself to get caught up in their roaming and poetic life (they’re war veterans who have difficulty settling down again in civilian life), and in their bloody fight against Chino’s Satan’s Slaves …
name: Hell's Angels

description: Mt. Cerro Puerto de Lajas is a sacred mountain in the Apache tradition. It’s here that Monty, Mister No’s Native American friend, wants to have his ashes scattered... And so, together with the young Apache John Kanteka Smith, Mister No sets out on a journey in quest of a glorious past that can never come back again. And what makes everything even more complicated is the meeting with a couple of brutal robbers who need two hostages in order to cross the border into Mexico...
name: Una Storia del West

description: In Ilha da Costa Baixa, a motorboat has been moored to a small pier for a very, very long time. Covered in vegetation, it has some human bones inside, memory of a tragic and bloody event. Mister No remembers it for good, since that was the beginning of everything… And that’s where Jerry will go back to, after a reckless flight and a thrilling escape in the jungle, chased by cruel gunmen who want him dead. Trailing along behind him it’s a client who – of course! – isn’t what he pretends to be …
name: Il Tesoro Maledetto

description: After their arrival in Rurrenabaque, Bolivia, Mister No and Esse-Esse try to rearrange their lives. But everyone knows it's always been hard for Jerry Drake to stay away from troubles. And troubles will come, as usual, just when he's not expecting them... A story that seemed to have come to an end, has a new, tragic, start. Old enemies looking for revenge will come hunting for Mister No, to involve him in a dramatic confrontation on board of the “Victoria”, the famous old ship moored on the river flowing through Nova Esperança. But, since a long time, the ship has become the headquarter of a blood-thirsty gang of Colombian criminals!
name: Il Clan dei Colombiani

description: The Sertão: a place where barely any vegetation can grow, but also a place where the seed of violence has been planted. Once again Mister No goes to North-eastern Brazil, after a night of partying in Salvador de Bahia. And he's unwillingly involved in the crossfire of two rival families who are looking for revenge. The Guimarães and the Duartes live in their proud and secluded world, where their fazendas are a lawless place of sorts, only ruled by a code of honour that states: blood calls blood!
name: Sangue sul Sertão

description: Mister No leads a thrill-seeking American tourists’ expedition through the jungle. But their exciting adventure will soon become a real nightmare! The Tucuna Indios are ready to kill all the white people they’ll find insider their land. But what’s the reason behind this unexpected violence? What stirred the rage of the warriors from such a peaceful tribe?
name: L’Assassino Misterioso

description: On the beaches of Cearà, Jerry Drake recalls an old adventure of his: it's the beginning of the 1950s, when the Amazonas pilot sets foot in Pecém for the first time. The poor local fishers see their existence threatened by the projects of big land-owners like the cynical Napoleòn Moureira. The fishers from Praia Grande decide to try a desperate rebellion. Only two idealist dreamers join their side: Captain Shangai Jack and Mister No!
name: Jangadas!

description: America's favorite family of superheroes ongoing series continues courtesy of Karl Kesel! Join Karl as he takes on the Parr family in an all-new Incredibles tale that takes the book in an all-new direction, and is sure to delight both adults and kids alike!

Witness the beginnings of the greatest Green Lantern of all in this new printing of the first chapter of "Secret Origin,"priced at just $1.00! Featuring art and story by the BLACKEST NIGHT team of Geoff Johns and Ivan Reis, this issue is collected in the GREEN LANTERN: SECRET ORIGIN TP.

Wendy, Dr. Harlow and Cross find themselves transported to the magical world of Neverland where they begin their quest to rescue Michael and John from Pan's island. Their search is side tracked when the meet the islands less then friendly natives. Meanwhile Pan contemplates has his own sinister plans for the boys. This issue is a must have for every Grimm and Wonderland fan!

Despite the way "Baka Shinji" makes them boil, Asuka didn't get her brains out of a gachapon machine, but from her mother, the brilliant but absent Dr. Kyoko Soryu. There could probably be less embarrassing places for a family reunion than at a drunken cherry-blossom-viewing party -- but unfortunately, Asuka isn't picking the occasion!
name: Volume 4

volume.name: Neon Genesis Evangelion: The Shinji Ikari Raising Project

description: Now, it’s important for a father to participate when it’s time for a parent-teacher conference, but you're still going to feel a little nervous as the student -- or, if your father’s name is Gendo Ikari, a lot nervous! While Shinji’s girl troubles continue to be a public spectacle, Kaworu and Ritsuko are going behind his back . . . straight to SEELE. Love, comedy, and mystery continue in volume 3.
name: Volume 3

volume.name: Neon Genesis Evangelion: The Shinji Ikari Raising Project

description: In part two of "Kozaki," both Sergius the pirate and the sadistic Shah Amurath decide to confront Conan's group of bandits, who are encroaching upon their territories and threatening the outlying granaries, farms, and villages of the proud country of Turan. King Yildiz quickly orders the Shah to annihilate all Kozaki riders, and Sergius arranges a parley with our favorite Cimmerian. In a tense meeting, Sergius explains how commerce works around the Vilayet Sea and offers that their two imposing forces work together against the Shah. With those in Conan's hungry crew growing wild and impatient, Conan's not even sure how long he can keep his own men together -- but he'll slit the throat of any who try to defect!
name: Kozaki (Part 2)

description: After warring for a century, Earth's greatest champions and villains suddenly disappear, leaving the planet decimated. Like a rapture, the Powers are gone and humanity is left behind to pick up the pieces. Amongst this wreckage, two lovers, Evelyn and Gil, find themselves separated by a continent and will do anything to find each other again. But when a strange being named "the Word" turns Evelyn into a champion with an angelic spear, she finds the force of her love for Gil clashing with her newfound power. Love and destiny collide in what will become the worst breakup ever!
name: TPB

description: The rabbit ronin's warrior pilgrimage brings him to a new town, with new friends and new threats, in this standalone tale! Having returned to the road, a rainstorm sends Usagi in search of shelter. Finding a town, Usagi meets Taro, a young maker of tera tera bozu-dolls that children construct to ensure good weather. Little Taro hangs one up on the eaves so that he and his new long-eared friend can play in the morning. The next day may turn out to be fine, but the night could be a killer.
name: Teru Teru Bozu

description:
1. Barney and Betty Rubble - The Mod Scientist - 6 pages

2. Barney and Betty Rubble - Road Test - 3 pages

3. Barney and Betty Rubble - Second Chance - 1 page

4. Barney and Betty Rubble - Who's Up, Doc? - 2 pages

5. Barney and Betty Rubble - Knot Up to Par - 3 pages

6. Barney and Betty Rubble - A Real Pane - 1 page

7. Barney and Betty Rubble - Paws - 6 pages (Jaws Parody)

8. Barney and Betty Rubble - Who Am I? - 2 page text story
name: The Mod Scientist

description: The world's attention is focused painfully on a brutal third-world civil war, a merciless sectarian conflict sparing neither soldier nor civilian, grandmother nor child. But amidst the terror and carnage, where great nations and powerful interests jockey for position and advantage, another blood feud rages in the shadows, one no more humane but decidedly less human. Two warring tribes from the stars have chosen Earth's killing fields as their arena, with each clan sworn to eradicate the other . . . and all who stand between them. Each is the other's prey, each the other's Predator. The hunt resumes as Dark Horse Books unleashes Predator once again into the graphic-fiction jungle. Features the creative team of writer John Arcudi (Aliens, B.P.R.D., Doom Patrol) and artist Javier Saltares (Aliens vs. Predator, Ghost Rider).
name: TPB

description:
The Sith poison the waters of the ocean planet of Dac in an effort to wipe out every living thing-but Admiral Gar Stazi isn't ready to abandon the native Mon Calamari without an attempt at evacuation. Time is against him, and securing the assistance of his new Imperial allies will decide whether this rescue is a success . . . or a suicide! The Rogue Squadron returns!

Darth Wyyrlok is greeted with the news that Darth Krayt is missing.
name: The Fate Of Dac

description: It was a beautiful spring day in downtown San Francisco before a gigantic armored alien appeared from out of nowhere and began smashing things all to hell! Who is this invader? Why is he being attacked by strange alien beings? And why is he so Gigantic? A twist on The Truman Show, Gigantic focuses on a brainwashed alien superhero deposited on Earth to be the spotlight of an intrusive, around-the-clock television program being filmed without his knowledge.

1. Nobody There! (hosted by The Old Witch / written by Albert B. Feldstein : reprinted from: Haunt of Fear (EC,1950) #16)
 
2. A Creep in the Deep! (hosted by The Vault Keeper / written by Albert B. Feldstein : reprinted from: Haunt of Fear (EC,1950) #16) 
 
3. ... From Hunger! (hosted by The Old Witch / written by Albert B. Feldstein : reprinted from: Haunt of Fear (EC,1950) #16) 
 
4. The Coffin! (hosted by The Crypt Keeper / adapted from a Ray Bradbury story by Albert B. Feldstein : reprinted from: Haunt of Fear (EC,1950) #16)
name: Nobody There!

description: In the barely-remembered time before the Terminators, the life of a young woman key to humanity's survival depends on the actions of Kyle Reese in present-day 2029. But Kyle may not live long enough to help Sarah Conner if he and his companions Ben and Paige can't escape Skynet's terrifying new weapon-Terminators that look just like people! Guided by information about a hidden Cyberdyne facility, the three friends must brave T-800s, HKs, rogue resistance gangs, and other threats in their search for any advantage against the machines. What they can't anticipate is the nature of the incredible resource hidden within the facility's walls!

Cover: Paul Marshall (Judge Dredd)
